Empresas Publicas de Medellin SAâ€™s
telecommunications unit plans to sell as much as 300 billion
pesos ($158 million) worth of inflation-linked bonds in the
local market tomorrow.  UNE EPM Telecomunicaciones SA, or UNE, as the company is
known, will offer 200 billion pesos worth of the securities and
make an additional 100 billion pesos available if there is
sufficient demand, according to a statement published today in
 La Republica  newspaper. UNE will offer five- and 12-year
securities linked to inflation and will use the resources to
fund its investments, according to the statement. Correval SA
brokerage is managing the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
